The paper focuses on autonomous navigation of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) in outdoor environments, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed solution involves using image classification algorithms (cs.CV) and imitation learning (cs.LG) to train the UAV to navigate through city streets. The paper also mentions the use of data-driven solutions (cs.AI) and the need for autonomy in UAVs (cs.SY).
